interactions.flavorLineOne: Emperor Calus was delighted to have you aboard the Leviathan again. You are always welcome at his table.

The "Crown of Sorrow" raid is now active.

One of the Emperor's Loyalists believed he could control an Ascendant artifact. Now the Hive control him. Put Gahlran, the Sorrow-Bearer out of his misery and reclaim the Crown.

You present Gahlran's helmet to the frame.

Calus speaks through it, as ever. He alludes vaguely to something that he saw out at the edge of the universe during his exile, something that he calls "the truth of the universe."

You'll need to cultivate a greater sense of appreciation for such truths. Perhaps if you spend more time with the Emperor, you'll learn more.
Calus is interested by your alliance with the Awoken of the Reef. Should the opportunity arise, he wants you to "put in a good word" for him.

Benedict stops sweeping and turns to face you. "His Highness sends his good wishes for you at this celebrated time of year," he says. "The Great Emperor rejoices in the overwhelming inevitability of death and is pleased that the Guardian-tribe does the same."

He turns and continues to sweep. "Feast and be merry in the Emperor's name."
"### Vzzzzt. Imperial Majesty  threat detected. Weaponsmith  continuing threat. Remove #&&_obstacle now. Reap the reward from his Highness." Benedict 99-40

Benedict's eye pulses red in syncopated rhythm, solidifying upon your approach.

"You'll be pleased to know your efforts were not in vain and the weapon has been located. Emperor Calus would be satisfied if you could cavort to the Quarry Lost Sector (Legendary) in the EDZ to recover it. In celebration of his decadence, indulge in a merciless spree of Red Legion desecration. Spread delight in his Eminence's name."
"vvvwwwweell done. His Royal Highness bids you show_$%& your loyalty. Use his gift to end the traitorzzzzzz." Benedict 99-40
"kkkkkkzk still much to prove to his Highness. Return to the Leviathan. Seek glory in his nammmme." Benedict 99-40
"You have not yettttt faced the _#*&% greatest challenge his Highness has to offer." Benedict 99-40

Steam emanates from the head of the frame as its piercing red eye raises to meet yours.

"Ah, Guardian. The Exalted One anticipated your cooperation in his grand design. With his infinite wisdom, he requests your assistance in furthering his machinations. His Excellency intended to use the weapon to eliminate Red Legionnaires. It seems you share a mutual goal."

Benedict's body turns and resets.

"Unfortunately, the Shadow you seek has been disposed of. Calus's insubordinate daughter, Caiatl, dispatched a countermeasuremuch to the Glorious One's displeasure. The weapon is lost. I can compile the data you've brought me of the deceased Shadow's log, but it is heavily encrypted. Encryption signals point toward the EDZ. Perhaps you can perform some unscrambling?"

Calus is pleased by your swift progress, but the potential of the Chalice of Opulence far exceeds your efforts today.

Only by entering Calus's Menagerie on the Leviathan will you begin to unlock its true abilities.

As Calus speaks through Werner 99-40's stolen body, the frame offers you a fragmented Chalice.

Calus invites you to restore the Chalice, a symbol of power for his Shadowselite Imperial assassins, the epitome of their respective alien races.

As Benedict's core processes seem to hitch and jitter, a commanding presence overtakes the poor frame. A different voice booms through Benedict's speakers.

Emperor Calus, the hedonistic ruler of the Leviathan, has been watching you for some time. He invites you to Nessus, offering riches.

Nothing suspicious about that!
"Scanning Tower inventory lists Seems like another maintenance frame went on the fritz and disappeared from the Hangar a day or two ago." Ghost
